<para>
  The isotropic dielectric permittivity &property; specifies that the
  <xref linkend="Flux-Total_Polarization"/> &flux;,
  <inlineequation><alt role="tex">\(D\)</alt></inlineequation>, depends
  linearly and isotropically on the gradient of the <xref
  linkend="Field-Voltage"/> &field;, <inlineequation><alt
  role="tex">\(\phi\)</alt></inlineequation>:
  <equation>
    <alt role="tex">
      \[ D_i = \epsilon \frac{\partial\phi}{\partial x_i} \]
    </alt>
  </equation>
  where the permittivity <inlineequation><alt
  role="tex">\(\epsilon\)</alt></inlineequation> is given by the
  parameter <varname>epsilon</varname>.
</para>

